615951.title: Frankenweenie
615951.short_synopsis: When a boy's beloved dog passes away suddenly, he attempts to bring the animal back to life through a powerful science experiment.

745025.title: Longlegs (Halloween Re-release)
745025.short_synopsis: In pursuit of a serial killer, an FBI agent uncovers a series of occult clues that she must solve to end his terrifying killing spree.

751587.title: Lee
751587.short_synopsis: The story of Lee Miller, American photographer. Determined to document the truth of the Nazi regime, and in spite of the odds stacked against female correspondents.

751728.title: The Outrun
751728.short_synopsis: After living life on the edge in London, Rona attempts to come to terms with her troubled past. She returns to the beauty of Scotland's Orkney Islands where she grew up.

752539.title: The Substance
752539.short_synopsis: Winner of best screenplay at Cannes 2024. Deliriously entertaining and ruthlessly satirical, Coralie Fargeat’s Cannes sensation turns toxic beauty culture inside out.

754298.title: 1999 Season: The Blair Witch Project
754298.short_synopsis: Three film students vanish after traveling into a Maryland forest to film a documentary on the local Blair Witch legend, leaving only their footage behind.

754299.title: Shaun of the Dead (20th Anniversary)
754299.short_synopsis: There comes a day in every man's life when he has to get off the couch…and kill some zombies. We'll meet you at The Winchester and wait for all of this to blow over...

755666.title: The Apprentice
755666.short_synopsis: The origins of Donald Trump are brought to life in a provocative, electrifying portrait of the man and his mentor, Roy Cohn – a notorious lawyer.

755667.title: Gladiator
755667.short_synopsis: See Ridley Scott's original 2000 epic back on the big screen at the Electric, ahead of the release of Gladiator II on November 15th.

755711.title: The Wild Robot
755711.short_synopsis: The Wild Robot follows a futuristic robot that washes ashore on a deserted island. A tale of survival and discovery begins.

755712.title: Smile 2
755712.short_synopsis: About to embark on a new world tour, global pop sensation Skye Riley (Naomi Scott) begins experiencing increasingly terrifying and inexplicable events.

755713.title: Venom: The Last Dance
755713.short_synopsis: Eddie and Venom are on the run. Hunted by both of their worlds and with the net closing in, the duo are forced into a devastating decision.

756672.title: Heretic
756672.short_synopsis: Two young missionaries are forced to prove their faith when they knock on the wrong door and are greeted by a diabolical Mr. Reed becoming ensnared in his deadly game.

756696.title: Anora
756696.short_synopsis: Anora, a sex worker from Brooklyn, gets her chance at a Cinderella story when she meets and marries the son of an oligarch.

756697.title: The Room Next Door
756697.short_synopsis: A best-selling writer reconnects with her mother after losing touch with her for a number of years. The latest from director Pedro Almodovar.

756729.title: Paddington in Peru
756729.short_synopsis: Paddington comes back home to the Peruvian jungle to visit his beloved Aunt Lucy, now a resident at the Home for Retired Bears.

756730.title: Gladiator II
756730.short_synopsis: Years after witnessing the death of the revered hero Maximus at the hands of his uncle, Lucius (Paul Mescal) is forced to enter the Colosseum after his home is conquered.

EV.title: Special Event
EV.popupText: Enjoy special screenings featuring live music, Q&A sessions, themed evenings and more.

MP.title: Members Preview
MP.popupText: Exclusive screenings for Soho House members at Portobello. Members screening places will be available to book online from 12pm a week before the screenings via the Soho House website or app, and can be collected from the Box Office on the day. Electric White City also runs members screening daily (Except Tuesday), and Soho Friends screenings on Tuesdays - The full programme for these is available on the Soho House app. Please call the box office for more information.

KC.title: Kids Club
KC.popupText: On production of a valid membership card, Electric House, White City House and Every House members receive two free tickets to our Kids Club screenings. Additional tickets can be purchased at £8 each. Please note adults purchasing Kids Club tickets must be accompanied by a child or will not be admitted. All Kids Club tickets must be purchased directly from the box office either by phone or in person.
KC.booking_intro_text: Please note that this is a Kids Club screening, adults purchasing tickets must be accompanied by a child/children or they will not be admitted.
KC.booking_confirm_checkbox: I understand that Adults purchasing tickets must be accompanied by a child or will not be admitted.

ES.title: Electric Scream!
ES.popupText: Electric Scream! screenings, for parents and carers and their babies under one year old, take place on Monday afternoons at the Electric Portobello, and Tuesday afternoons at the Electric White City. Please note adults purchasing Electric Scream! tickets must be accompanied by a baby under one year old or will not be admitted. All Electric Scream tickets must be purchased directly from the box office either by phone or in person.
ES.booking_intro_text: Please note that this is an Electric Scream! screening, adults purchasing tickets must be accompanied by a baby or they will not be admitted.
ES.booking_confirm_checkbox: I understand that adults purchasing tickets for Electric Scream! screenings must be accompanied by a baby or they will not be admitted and that prams or buggies must be left outside the auditorium at Electric White City.

EA.title: Electric Subtitled
EA.popupText: Electric Subtitled screenings for the hearing impaired take place on Tuesday at Portobello and Tuesday & Wednesday at White City.
EA.booking_intro_text: Please note that this is an Electric Subtitled screening for the hearing impaired and screenings will be shown with subtitles.
EA.booking_confirm_checkbox: I understand that this is an Electric Subtitled screening for the hearing impaired and screenings will be shown with subtitles.

SC.title: Electric Sundays
SC.popupText: Enjoy special discounted rates on our Sunday matinée feature performances. A chance to catch up on some of the films you might have missed in recent weeks, or a screening of a classic.
